\dfrac{d}{dt} \mathrm{\left ( x^Tx \right)}=\mathrm{ x^T \dot{x}}+\mathrm{\dot{x}^Tx}=\mathrm{x^T(A+A^T)x} \implies \dfrac{d}{dt}\left ( \|x(t)\|^2 \right )=x^T(t)\left [ A(t)+A^T(t) \right ]x(t)
\left [ t_0 , t \right ]
\|x(t)\|^2 =\|x(t_0)\|^2 +\int_{t_0}^{t}x^T(s)\left [ A(s)+A^T(s) \right ]x(s)\mathrm{d}s
\|x(t)\|^2 \le \|x(t_0)\|^2 +\int_{t_0}^{t}\|x^T(s)\|\left  \|A(s)+A^T(s) \right \| \|x(s)\| \mathrm{d}s  
= \|x(t_0)\|^2 +\int_{t_0}^{t}\left  \|A(s)+A^T(s) \right \| \|x(s)\|^2\mathrm{d}s
